  "original_title": "\u0b90.\u0b8e\u0bae\u0bcd.\u0b8e\u0baa\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd  \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A message issued by the IMF chief",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Kristalina Georgieva, head of the IMF, said today (04) that she is pleased to have reached a staff-level agreement between the staff of the International Monetary Fund and the Sri Lankan authorities to support the country's economic policies.",
        "He indicated the above in a post on his official Twitter page.",
        "Last Thursday (01), IMF officials announced at a press conference held at the Central Bank that the Government of Sri Lanka and the International Monetary Fund have reached an agreement for a 48-month extended financial assistance of 2.9 billion US dollars.",
        "Commenting on it, the head of the International Monetary Fund also mentioned that this is an important development for Sri Lanka."
      ],
